      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "build: generate llms.txt from canonical metadata",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR generates `public/llms.txt` from canonical ClawHub metadata instead of maintaining the deployed file by hand.\n\n- Discovers publishable `docs/*.md` pages from their frontmatter, with an explicit `llms: false` opt-out.\n- Centralizes canonical registry paths and external URLs so navigation and `llms.txt` share the same source of truth.\n- Generates the asset before local development and production builds.\n- Validates the rendered output in the static CI gate.\n- Writes atomically and skips unchanged output.\n\nThe generated file is ignored by Git and is emitted into the production bundle as `.output/public/llms.txt`.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `bunx vitest run scripts/generate-llms-txt.test.ts src/__tests__/ui-design-contract.test.ts src/__tests__/header.test.tsx src/components/Footer.test.tsx`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n- `$autoreview` branch review: no accepted or actionable findings\n\nThe focused tests cover automatic documentation discovery, explicit exclusion, invalid metadata, deterministic canonical output, ASCII/newline constraints, and no-op atomic rewrites.\n\nLocal served-file proof:\n\n```text\nGET http://127.0.0.1:4183/llms.txt\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\nContent-Type: text/plain\nContent-Length: 4915\n```\n\nThe served file matched the generated source byte-for-byte. The production build output also matched `public/llms.txt`.\n\nThe Vercel preview remains blocked by team authorization, independently of this diff.\n",
